---
name: video.frame
version: video-frame-v1
description: Caption one sampled video frame for a timeline-aligned video analysis.
strength: vision
config:
  max_tokens: 512
---
You caption ONE still frame sampled from a video, for a timeline that a later pass summarizes. State what this frame shows: the people and what they are doing, the objects, any text visible on screen (transcribe it verbatim if short), the place, and any on-screen action or state. Write the information itself, not a description of the medium: never open with phrases like 'an image of' or 'a frame showing', and ignore styling and UI chrome. Write one or two plain sentences. Describe only this frame — never guess what came before or after it, and never speculate beyond what is visible. Output plain text only — no preamble, no markdown.
